<!-- Whitespace in Webdesign: An Example -->
<div class="row">
<div class="col-lg-1 col-lg-offset-1 text-right">

</div>
<div class="col-lg-8">
<h1>Whitespace in Webdesign: An Example</h1>

<h2><small><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-time"></span> Published on May 19, 2014</small></h2>
<h3><small><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-tags"></span> Whitespace</small></h3>

<blockquote class="intro">
<p><i>Minimalist or modern designs tend toward more use of white space. White space or negative space is the space between design elements. On a macro level it's the space around the design and the large blocks of empty space between elements. On a micro level it's the space between two lines of text or the space between an image and its caption.</i></p>
</blockquote>

<ul class="list-unstyled para">
<li><h4>Read the full article</h4></li>
<li><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-link"></span> <a target="_blank" href="http://debashisbarman.tumblr.com/post/86189526364/whitespace-in-webdesign-an-example">Whitespace in Webdesign: an Example</a></li>
</ul>

</div>
</div>
